<h2>Mortgage Calculator</h2>

<section class='intro'>
<p>We'll need you to have the following information available: the Principal Amount; the Interest Rate and the Number of Payments you want to set the mortgage over.</p>
<p>We'll give you back the monthly payment you'll need to make.</p><br>
</section>

<section class='active_mortgage' id='mortgage'>
  <form action='/mortgage' method='get'>
    <p>What is the principal amount?</p>
    <input type='number' name='principal' placeholder='What is the amount you would like to borrow?'>
    </br>
    <p>What is the interest rate?</p>
    <input type='number' name='i_rate' placeholder='%'>
    </br>
    <p>How many years would you like to take the mortgage over?</p>
    <input type='number' name='payment_yrs' placeholder='Years'>
    <br><br>
    <button>submit</button>
  </form>
</section>

<% if @mortgage_result && @mortgage_result > 0 %>
  <section>
    <h2>Result</h2>
    <p>
      You will have to pay your mortgage back in monthly payments of Â£<%= @mortgage_result.round(2) %>
    </p>
  </section>
<% end %>